16/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO Ambassador to Macedonia Nicolaas Biegman said on Monday (15 September) that the country's prospects for joining the Alliance in 2006 are real. Speaking at a high-level forum in Skopje, Biegman added that Macedonia would have to prove its ability to maintain a peaceful and secure environment before it comes close to NATO membership.
In other news, Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski insisted Monday that partners in the ruling coalition have managed to overcome problems and that the government can control the security situation. His remarks came on the first anniversary of the formation of the multiethnic coalition government. (Utrinski Vesnik - 16/09/03; MIA, Makfax - 15/09/03)
